Burundian nationals staying in Kenya since 1959 complain of biased treatment and harassment from Kenyan authorities for lacking Kenya national identity card. Led by Kiza Shadrach, the Burundians complained that some of them are discriminated when accessing government services for the lack of identification documents. The more than 1 600 residing from Kwale county now want the Kenyan government to issue them with Kenyan identity cards the way it did to the Makonde people who originated from Malawi. --ChannelAfrica--